WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.520 --> 00:00:04.040
There's a feud between Iran and the West

00:00:04.040 --> 00:00:08.240
that’s spanned coups, sanctions and standoffs.

00:00:08.240 --> 00:00:10.680
“The world's number one state sponsor of terror.”

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:13.240
“Covert operation to overthrow Mossadegh.”

00:00:13.240 --> 00:00:15.360
“A Shah who had fled to Rome, comes home.”

00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:17.600
“Hundreds of thousands take to the streets.”

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:21.200
“1979 turned everything upside down.”

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:24.640
But it didn't start in 1979.

00:00:24.640 --> 00:00:30.360
Or with Mossadegh, or even with Iran.

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:33.080
“The largest empire the world had ever seen.”

00:00:33.080 --> 00:00:33.880
It goes back

00:00:33.880 --> 00:00:37.480
over 2000 years to the Persian Empire.

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:40.960
That's where we find one of the oldest stories

00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:42.360
ever told.

00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:44.640
The battle of good versus evil

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:46.080
“Erased from history.”

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:48.160
Of freedom versus tyranny.

00:00:48.160 --> 00:00:51.680
Of valiant West versus despotic East.

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:53.680
“And it’s the victors who write the history books.”

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:56.680
“The thousand nations of the Persian Empire

00:00:56.680 --> 00:00:58.080
descend upon you.”

00:00:59.280 --> 00:01:00.840
This origin story helps us

00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:02.640
understand what has been unfolding

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:06.200
for the past century, continuing into today.

00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:08.520
So if you want to understand

00:01:08.520 --> 00:01:11.480
why the West hates Persia,

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:17.120
first you have to understand

00:01:17.120 --> 00:01:19.560
why it worships Greece.

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:23.160
